Bernard HARRIS, Appellant, v. H. F. BAKER, Trustee in Bankruptcy of Bernard Harris, Appellee. No. 8024. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Nov. 16, 1935. J. Oscar Goldstein, of Chico, Cal., and Arthur P. Shapro, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. A. D. Schaffer and Torregano & Stark, all of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, DENMAN, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered, appeal dismissed; mandate forthwith.
